    <title>Scattering amplitude annihilators</title>
    <summary>  Several polynomial differential operators are shown to annihilate the
dimension-neutral YM and GR tree scattering amplitudes. In particular, we prove
a conjecture of Loebbert, Mojaza and Plefka from their investigation of a
hidden conformal symmetry in GR. The amplitudes are defined using a recursion
based on factorization of residues. (In the current version we assume without
proof that a solution to the recursion exists.)
</summary>
